- title('Edit the site info')

div.left
    :markdown
        ## Edit the site info

        Just open the `config.json` file and start editing it to your needs.

    dl
      dt name
      dd Used for the logo and page <code>#{'<title>'}</code> tag

      dt code (optional)
      dd Creates a button "See the code" in the header pointing to the url provided

      dt github (optional)
      dd Same as code but with the text "See on github"

      dt bitbucket (optional)
      dd Same as code but with the text "See on bitbucket"

      dt download (optional)
      dd Creates a button "Download" in the header pointing to your download

      dt menu (optional)
      dd 
        | If you want plan on having multiple page on your site, you can define a menu by setting the <code>menu</code> config and passing it an array of objects. Each object takes the following attributes:
        ul
          li
            strong title: 
            | The title of the menu item
          li
            strong url: 
            | The url of the menu item
          li
            strong class: 
            | The css class of the menu item (required)
          li
            strong children: 
            | An array of objects very much like the <code>menu</code> one. This will cause a sliding menu with the children items to open when you mouseover the menu item.

    div.hint
      :markdown
        Bibliosoph comes with the [TWG icon set](http://blog.twg.ca/2010/11/retina-display-icon-set/) (optimized for the web). To add an icon to a menu item, add something like this to your css:

        ```
        .my-menu-item-class span { 
          background: url('../images/icons/the-desired-icon.png') no-repeat 0 0;
        }
        ```

    div.hint
      :markdown
        When you edit css, we recommend to create a new file that you add in the `css/style.styl` file. It will the automatically be imported. Do not overwrite Bibliosoph stylus files as the customization would be lost if you ever update Bibliosoph.




div.right
    :markdown
        ### Exemple of a config.json
        ```json
        {
            "site": {
                "name"      : "Bibliosoph",
                "code"      : "http://yourprojectcodeurl.com",
                "github"    : "http://yourprojectgithuburl.com",
                "bitbucket" : "http://yourprojectbitbucketurl.com",
                "download"  : "http://yourprojectdownloadurl.com",
                "menu"      : [
                    {
                        "title"     : "Manifesto",
                        "url"       : "/manifesto",
                        "class"     : "manifesto"
                    },
                    {
                        "title"     : "Components",
                        "url"       : "/components",
                        "class"     : "components",
                        "children"  : [
                            {
                                "title"   : "Component 1",
                                "url"     : "/components/component-1",
                                "class"   : "component-1"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
        ```